description: The Allahabad High Court nullified the conviction and four-year sentence of Ghazipur MP Afzal Ansari in a Gangsters' Act case related to BJP MLA Krishnanand Rai's 2005 murder. The decision removes uncertainty regarding Afzal's Lok Sabha membership. Despite previous convictions, he was acquitted of Rai's murder in 2019, although the CBI has appealed this in Delhi HC.
title: Mukhtar Ansari's brother stays an MP as high court junks conviction

description: Paramjeet Singh Bisht, a 23-year-old from Khalla village in Uttarakhand, faced ridicule while training for the men's 20km race walk. Despite challenges, he honed his talent with support from his school coach and will now represent India at the Paris Olympics. Bisht is also a national record holder and enlisted in the Navy under the sports quota.
title: Uttarakhand village to Paris: A long walk to Oly glory

description: An IIT Bombay professor, Chetan Solanki, experienced the impact of climate change firsthand when his flight from Leh was cancelled due to unusually high temperatures. This highlights the growing issues of global warming, even affecting high-altitude areas like Ladakh. Airlines cited reduced air density and engine performance issues at such altitudes as the reasons for flight cancellations.
title: Heat & height deadly mix for plane engines

description: The government informed Rajya Sabha that the clarification on the requirement for a married woman to obtain an NOC from her husband to revert to her maiden surname aimed to avoid legal issues. This follows a woman's petition challenging the notification in Delhi high court, which is set for hearing on August 7th.
title: Government states why woman needs hubby's NOC for name change
Biden commemorates Civil Rights Act anniversary at LBJ Library

description: The Supreme Court rejected Bihar's plea to increase quotas for SCs, STs, and OBCs in state jobs and educational institutions from 50% to 65%. This decision followed a Patna High Court ruling deeming the law unconstitutional.
title: Supreme Court refuses to stay high court order quashing hike in Bihar quota

description: India and its Quad partners recently urged China to respect international maritime laws during a meeting in Tokyo. They discussed enhancing regional maritime security and expanding the Indo-Pacific Partnership for Maritime Domain Awareness to the Indian Ocean. The ministers emphasized collaboration, sovereignty, and territorial integrity, while also addressing debt crises and opposing unilateral force in regional waters.
title: Only Quad can ensure a free Indo-Pacific: S Jaishankar

description: Sharad Pawar, NCP (SP) chief, voiced concerns about potential disturbances in Maharashtra similar to those in Manipur, urging societal unity. He criticized the Centre's handling of Manipur's ethnic strife and reiterated worries about community rifts over quota issues. BJP's Chandrashekar Bawankule deemed Pawar's remarks inappropriate and potentially inflammatory.
title: Maharashtra may see Manipur-like unrest, says Sharad Pawar

description: The Supreme Court issued a notice to the Ajit Pawar group, which the Election Commission recognized as the true NCP, on a petition challenging the Maharashtra Speaker's refusal to disqualify MLAs for joining the ruling coalition. The Speaker's decision was criticized for allegedly subverting Supreme Court directives despite the approaching assembly elections.
title: Supreme Court notice to Ajit faction in NCP feud over MLA disqualification

description: The Supreme Court was informed that a 287th rank-holder in the INICET missed a PG seat at AIIMS, Delhi, which was given to a 10,721 ranker. This was due to AIIMS erroneously treating 'institutional preference' as a form of reservation. The court had previously ruled against institutional reservation but allowed up to 50% preference.
title: 'AIIMS flouts SC rulings, gives seat preference to own docs'

description: The Madhya Pradesh High Court ruled that individuals in non-government jobs receiving regular increments can be considered permanent employees. The court increased compensation for Anjum Ansari by Rs 2.7 lakh after her claim under the Motor Vehicles Act, acknowledging her husband's status as a permanent teacher in a private college.
title: Private employees with periodic hikes deemed permanent: High court

description: Government moved forward with significant structural and functional changes for the Defence Research and Development Organization (DRDO) based on recommendations by an expert committee. Around 60% of the proposed reforms have been accepted, focusing on core R&D activities, while contentious measures are pending final approval.
title: DRDO overhaul on course, govt to also take final call on 'contentious' reforms

description: Quad addressed the Gaza situation amid rising Israel-Hezbollah tensions, calling for hostages' release and a ceasefire. India issued an advisory for nationals in Lebanon. The Quad meeting also covered Ukraine's humanitarian crisis, urging respect for sovereignty. Focused on West Asia, they emphasized peace, stability, and a two-state solution for Israel and Palestine.
title: Quad bats for peace in Gaza and Ukraine; EAM says more contact likely with Ukraine and Russia

description: In Tokyo, foreign ministers from India, the US, Australia, and Japan voiced concerns over China's actions in the South China Sea during a Quad meeting. They called for an Indo-Pacific region free from dominance, upholding the 2016 tribunal ruling against China. The ministers discussed enhancing maritime security and announced initiatives to expand regional maritime domain awareness.
title: Quad raps China for SCS manoeuvres, backs Philippines

description: New restrictions on mediapersons in Parliament led to an uproar, with opposition leader Rahul Gandhi urging the Speaker to lift the constraints. Congress deputy leader Gaurav Gogoi also opposed the restrictions and requested the removal of post-Covid access limits for journalists. Speaker Om Birla assured that grievances would be addressed with better facilities for journalists.
title: Free media from cage, says Rahul as fresh Parliament curbs spark row

description: The Defence Ministry approved the procurement of about 970 advanced land navigation systems for Army armoured vehicles and 22 interceptor boats for the Coast Guard. The navigation systems, provided by Bharat Electronics Ltd, Chennai, offer high encryption and accuracy. The interceptor boats aim to enhance the Coast Guard's coastal surveillance capabilities.
title: Acquisition of 970 navigation systems, 22 interceptor boats gets nod

description: Rahul Gandhi engaged in a heated exchange during a speech, clashing with ministers and Speaker Om Birla. He humorously navigated the prohibition on naming non-members by referring to Adani and Ambani as 'A1 and A2'. Parliamentary Affairs Minister Kiren Rijiju criticized Rahul for his actions, but Rahul retorted that Rijiju was acting on orders from higher authorities.
title: LOP's barbs spark clashes with ministers, Speaker in LS

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized the budget, claiming it failed to address unemployment, education, and pension issues for Agniveers. He highlighted the absence of SC/ST/OBC representation in the finance ministry's budget photo, emphasizing the need for a caste census. He accused the BJP of creating a 'chakravyuh' to trap various societal segments and promised to counter it with inclusive policies.
title: Farmers, youth trapped in ‘chakravyuh’, but will break free: Rahul in Lok Sabha

description: Defence minister Rajnath Singh accused Rahul Gandhi of misleading the country on national security and the Agnipath initiative after Rahul's Budget speech in Lok Sabha. Singh offered to clarify in Parliament, addressing concerns over compensation for Agniveers killed in action. Rahul disputed Singh's claims about the monetary support for Agniveer martyrs' families.
title: Rahul misleading nation on Agnipath, says Rajnath, offers statement in House

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar, during a press briefing in Tokyo, emphasized that the India-China border dispute is a bilateral issue and should be resolved between the two nations. He dismissed the need for third-party intervention, despite global interest. Jaishankar mentioned recent discussions with Chinese foreign minister Wang Yi and stressed the importance of direct dialogue.
title: Jaishankar rules out role for 3rd party in India-China row

description: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath urged kanwariyas to exercise self-discipline during their pilgrimage, emphasizing internal and external devotion. He highlighted the extensive arrangements by central and state governments for a smooth yatra, including enhanced patrolling, cleanliness, and health camps. The kanwar yatra, held from July 22 to August 6, is a period of deep devotion for Lord Shiva's followers.
title: Amid troubles by kanwariyas, UP CM calls for self-discipline

description: A government primary school teacher in Aligarh was suspended for 'irresponsible behavior' after videos showed her taking a nap during class and caning students. The investigation revealed she wasn’t feeling well and had fallen. She claimed the parent had requested the beating. The school official who filmed the videos was also terminated.
title: Napping teacher suspended, staffer who took video sacked

description: Deputy chief of Shiv Sena (UBT) Thane unit, Milind More died from a suspected heart attack after a violent clash at a resort in Navapur. Following his death, officials demolished illegal structures at the resort, claiming prior notices were issued. Seven arrests were made. The incident was captured on CCTV, and police are awaiting the postmortem report.
title: Thane UBT neta dies after group clash, officials raze parts of Virar resort

description: The NEET counselling for undergraduate medical seats began on August 14. The process is scheduled in four rounds, concluding on October 30. This year, the exam faced a controversy over an alleged paper leak, but the Supreme Court dismissed the pleas for a re-test. Over 23 lakh students appeared for the May exam, seeking admission to around 1.2 lakh seats.
title: For 1.2 lakh seats on offer, 4-round NEET-UG counselling from August 14

description: Manika Batra achieved a historic feat on Monday by advancing to the round of 16 in the Olympic Games singles competition, a first for an Indian table tennis player.
title: Manika first Indian TT player to reach last 16 in Olympics

description: A special court sentenced former Assam Public Service Commission chairman Rakesh Paul to 14 years of rigorous imprisonment for a cash-for-job scam. Two other APSC members received 10-year sentences, and 29 convicted candidates got four years each. This stems from allegations made in 2017 by an unsuccessful candidate questioning the selection process for agricultural development officer jobs in Assam government.
title: Cash-for-job scam: Former Assam official gets 14-years jail

description: The Rajasthan education department's academic calendar now marks Aug 5 as Swarna Mukut Mastak Diwas to commemorate the 2019 abrogation of Article 370. Additional notable dates include Savarkar Jayanti, Surya Namaskar Diwas, and Desh Prem Diwas. Congress criticized the move, claiming it politicizes education. The state parents' association also voiced concerns over the calendar.
title: Celebrate Art 370 abrogation on August 5: Rajasthan to govt schools

description: A 50-year-old American woman, Lalita Kayi, was found chained to a tree in Maharashtra's Sindhudurg district. She appeared frail, with mental health prescriptions and expired visa documents in her possession. Authorities suspect her husband fled after tying her. She was hospitalized and is now out of danger. A case is yet to be registered.
title: Tied to tree, US woman found abandoned in Maharashtra forest amid rain

description: A committee supervising the inventory of Puri Jagannath temple's Ratna Bhandar suspected that duplicate keys were used in the past to steal valuables. Committee member Jagdish Mohanty indicated a criminal intent after locks malfunctioned. The Ratna Bhandar inventory inspection revealed several locked almirahs and chests, sparking concerns over past theft attempts.
title: Puri Ratna Bhandar theft not ruled out: Member of inventory panel

description: Cabinet secretary Rajiv Gauba instructed all secretaries to ensure invited officials attend the Independence Day celebration at Red Fort. Gauba emphasized that absences would be taken seriously and reminded officers of their duty to participate in this national event. The advisory was issued to ensure better compliance this year, as many had previously failed to attend.
title: Babus skipping Independence-Day event may face action

description: Six Conservative MPs, including Priti Patel and Robert Jenrick, vied to replace Rishi Sunak as party leader. After nominations, the field included four men and two women. Suella Braverman withdrew despite sufficient support. The final two candidates will be chosen by party members in November, with Sunak remaining acting leader. Candidates faced rules to avoid personal attacks.
title: Priti Patel among MPs declared contenders in Tory leadership battle

description: Four scrap dealers died in Sopore, Kashmir, after discarded ammunition exploded during unloading. The consignment, sourced from Ladakh, caused instant fatalities and hospital deaths. Police have registered a case and are investigating the source. Forensic experts have been called to determine the explosive's nature. The incident incited panic in the Sher Colony locality.
title: 4 scrap dealers killed in blast triggered by discarded ammo in J&K
2 children dead, 9 injured after yoga workshop knife attack in UK's Southport

description: In Pakistan's Kurram tribal district, clashes over a land dispute escalated into sectarian violence between Sunni and Shia tribes, resulting in 43 deaths and over 200 injuries. A temporary ceasefire was achieved with the help of a local tribal jirga. The conflict led to food and medical shortages in many villages as authorities closed roads to contain the unrest.
title: 43 killed, 200 injured in Sunni-Shia clashes in Pakistan northwest since July 24

description: For a second day running, Manu Bhaker was the star of the India show as she combined with Sarabjot Singh to make the bronze medal match of the 10m air pistol mixed team competition at Chateauroux's shooting range.
title: India at Olympics: Bhaker in contention for another bronze; archers crumble

description: A woman in New Zealand was sentenced to two months in jail for overfeeding her dog to death. The dog, Nuggi, weighed 53.7kg and suffered severe health issues. Despite being rescued and losing weight, Nuggi passed away due to an acute hemorrhage. The SPCA criticized the owner's neglect and failure to provide proper care.

description: Snowball Earth refers to several global glaciation events that took place around 700 million years ago. During these times, the planet was encased in ice, creating harsh conditions for life. Despite this, it was also a period of significant biological change, leading to the emergence of multicellular organisms.  Carl Simpson, a paleobiologist from the University of Colorado, Boulder, suggests that the icy conditions of Snowball Earth made seawater much thicker and more challenging for tiny, single-celled organisms to navigate and find food.
title: Thanda Thanda Paani: Why cold water might have been key to life on earth

description: In the 56th minute, desperate to find the equalizer, India took their trusted custodian Sreejesh off the pitch to have an extra field-player in the form of attacker Gurjant Singh at their disposal. The move to bring an extra field-player into the attack did the trick for India, enabling a relentless attack on the Argentine circle and a video referral that gave India a penalty corner in the 59th minute. Skipper Harmanpreet Singh scored off it to earn India a point when all seemed lost.

description: The Ministry of Home Affairs formed a committee to investigate the deaths of three students who drowned in the flooded basement of a coaching center in Old Rajinder Nagar, New Delhi. The committee will consist of various officials and will submit its report in 30 days. The aim is to understand the reasons, fix responsibility, and recommend policy changes.
title: Coaching centre deaths: Centre forms probe panel, to submit report in 30 days

He called for immediate action to protect students' safety and requested a permanent solution to the recurring issue.

Following that he abruptly left the Indian Test team in South Africa, citing fatigue. He then missed India domestic cricket going against Indian cricket board's order. Ishan also had a poor IPL 2024 where he managed only 324 runs in 14 games and was then ignored for the T20 World Cup in the Americas which India won.

description: The Mughal Empire adeptly used architecture to stay cool without modern air conditioning. They employed flora, water, jharokhas, courtyards, thick walls, high ceilings, chhatris, domes, jaali screens, and strategic building orientation to regulate temperature and improve ventilation. The apex court noted that the high court delivered a well-reasoned order. The HC had observed that none of the records showed Soren's direct involvement in the alleged crime.

Bron Breakker and Sami Zayn's feud also intensified, and CM Punk awaited a confrontation with Drew McIntyre.

description: The Supreme Court issued a notice to the Bihar government responding to a petition demanding thorough structural audits of bridges to prevent frequent collapses. The plea, filed by advocate Brajesh Singh, cited negligence and corruption, urging either demolition or retrofitting of weak structures. The court demanded a response, highlighting urgent need for better infrastructure safety measures in the flood-prone state.

The woman claimed Deshmukh sexually assaulted her and extorted Rs 2.7 crore from a Navi Mumbai Shiv Sena functionary by instructing her to file a false rape case. description: The CBI filed a chargesheet against Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal in the excise policy case. Kejriwal remains in judicial custody till August 8. description: Manu Bhaker claimed a historic bronze medal in women's 10m air pistol event at the Paris Games, becoming the first female shooter from India to win an Olympic medal. This is India's fifth Olympic medal in shooting and the first since the 2012 London Olympics. Manu will compete in two more events in Paris - 10m air pistol mixed team and 25m pistol.
title: 'In training, I was fined 40 to 400 euros if...' - Manu Bhaker

description: ITR refund status FY 2023-24: If you've filed your ITR for the financial year 2023-24 and are waiting for your refund, you can now check the status of your refund on the income tax e-filing portal at incometax.gov.in.
title: How to check income tax refund status online in 3 easy steps

description: A United Airlines flight from Houston to Boston was diverted to Washington DC due to a biohazard incident. A passenger became ill, causing crew members to vomit and passengers to request masks. The plane landed safely for a deep clean, and no medical assistance was needed for the 155 passengers and six crew members.
title: ‘Biohazard’ on United Airlines flight: Crew vomiting, passengers ask for masks

description: Kenney Kelley won the Big Brother 26 Week 2 Power of Veto, saving himself from eviction. HOH Chelsie Baham's initial target was Lisa Weintraub. Chelsie now faces a challenging decision for the replacement nominee, as new eviction rules make predicting outcomes difficult. The live feed updates and A.I. Arena challenge add to the suspense of the week's proceedings.
title: Big Brother 26: Kenney Kelly wins the week 2 Power of Veto battle

description: The Indian cricket team's participation in the ICC Champions Trophy in Pakistan is a contentious issue due to the country's long-standing stance not to travel there. Former cricketers from both nations have raised concerns about the visit, with ex-Pakistan pacer Tanvir Ahmed referring to Pakistan's visit to India for the ODI World Cup last year.
title: 'Hum aa ke khel ke gaye hai': Ex-cricketer invites Team India to Pak

description: On Sunday, Manu, now 22, shot like a pro, like she has been for months now. No nerves, no excuses, no meltdown. She was in the zone, making history by becoming the first Indian woman shooter to win an Olympic medal — a bronze in 10m air pistol. The top two postions were secured by South Koranns; the gold went to Oh Ye Jin and the silver was won by Kim Yeji.
title: India's Paris Olympics 'Manu'script begins with bronze

description: India's cement industry is witnessing an intense battle as Gautam Adani's expansion efforts trigger a race with Kumar Mangalam Birla's UltraTech Cement Ltd. Both billionaires are striving to dominate the supply of cement, crucial for India's infrastructure boom. In less than two years, Adani and UltraTech have completed six deals, with UltraTech announcing a seventh acquisition of a key regional player.
title: Billionaire battle heats up as Adani challenges Birla in cement

description: Aakash Babu, a 29-year-old auto driver, saved 55 residents by alerting them about the building collapse in Navi Mumbai. His prompt actions initially met reluctance, but residents soon heeded his warnings. Previously avoided due to his 'drinking habit,' Babu is now appreciated for his life-saving efforts during the incident.
title: Belapur building crash: How alert auto driver saved 55 lives

description: Goa has transformed from a laidback haven to a luxury real estate hotspot due to the new Manohar International Airport. The airport has spurred infrastructure projects and investor interest, leading to upscale developments and rising property prices in northern Goa, appealing primarily to affluent buyers from major Indian cities like Mumbai, Pune, Bengaluru, and Delhi.
title: Now boarding: Realty bonanza’s direct flight to Goa’s Mopa region

description: Ravichandran Ashwin was involved in a humorous incident during a TNPL 2024 match. Bowler Mohan Prasath warned Ashwin for leaving the non-striker's end too early, but he kept his bat grounded until the last moment. The incident amused both spectators and commentators, as commentators couldn't contain their laughter during the on-air commentary.
title: 'Headmaster' Ashwin receives 'Mankad warning' in TNPL - Watch
